			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I don't know if this has been pointed our already but I'm going to say it anyhow (don't feel like reading everything)  This spell is great for soloing beasts.  When you get this spell at level 4 you might find some yellow bears so let's use them as an example. You have your pet ready, cast Tashan on the bear to draw it in, let it hit you so your pet attacks it, back up and cast your DoT on the bear and just wait. When it wears off cast the DoT again. Sooner or later you pet may die and the bear comes after you. This is when you use color flux to stun the bear and recast your pet. Now if the bear is STILL coming after you and not the pet, Cast color flux again, then Mezz it so it forgets about you. Now your pet and DoTs can finish the pet off.  This might not work well at level  4 since you don't have a great deal of mana, but a bear isn't that hard to kill.  Small warning poison wielding mobs are more dangerous, if they hit you and poison you it doesn't matter if you stun it, the poison will still do it's work. I try to avoid these fellows =)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
